WEBVTT

00:06:29.102 --> 00:06:32.101
to become these memory champions.

00:06:32.125 --> 00:06:35.518
And I wanted to find out
whether I could do that too.

00:06:37.117 --> 00:06:38.965
AG: So Josh, with his spotty memory,

00:06:38.989 --> 00:06:41.712
started training
with a master of the sport,

00:06:41.736 --> 00:06:44.085
and eventually wrote a book
about the experience,

00:06:44.109 --> 00:06:46.283
called "Moonwalking with Einstein."

00:06:46.307 --> 00:06:47.855
JF: They weren't making this up.

00:06:47.879 --> 00:06:53.291
It is absolutely true that when you learn
these memory techniques,

00:06:53.315 --> 00:06:55.578
you can perform
astounding feats of memory.

00:06:55.602 --> 00:06:58.950
And this is verified
not just by my own experience,

00:06:58.974 --> 00:07:04.155
but by, like, 2,500 years of history
of people using these techniques,